THE ASUARCA. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 16, 1923.) No. 274. Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell; Hickox & Keating, of New York City (Robert S. Erskine, John M. Woolsey, and Harry D. Thirkield, all of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Bigliam, Englar & Jones, of New York City (T. Catesby Jones and William H. Woolley, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellees.

Before ROGERS, MANTON, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
